&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TITLE OF POST:                   Service Manager – Medical Records &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GRADE:                                  Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SALARY:                                £38,890 - £44,503 pro rata &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DEPARTMENT:                    Access – Medical Records&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HOURS:                                 37.5 Hours per week &lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BRIEF DESCRIPTION OF POST:                                         &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you an experienced professional with operational business planning and monitoring skills currently working in the NHS or wider public sector and looking to broaden your skills in a teaching foundation trust? &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Could you rise to the challenge we have to offer in shaping the strategic direction and development of the services provided by Medical Records across the Trust?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If yes, then we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will include operational business planning and monitoring, supporting the delivery of key projects, and the delivering of change. The post holder will ensure that the Medical Records Department functions are an integral part of the Trust and that Trust-wide objectives are achieved simultaneously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition you will work closely with a number of other teams overseeing specific pieces of work and line management duties as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The department is undergoing significant changes, the post holder will help drive and deliver those changes to ensure that the service is able to meet the demands of its stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will initially work alongside the General Manager, Head of Planned Access and the Medical Records team in re shaping the future of it as well as other key members of Planned Care. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for management of initially circa. 40 staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we will offer you a great opportunity to develop in the NHS with extensive exposure to all levels within the Foundation Trust and contact with external statutory bodies such as NHSi, the Care Quality Commission and the Department of Health.  This is a pivotal role to shape the strategic development of our services within Corporate Operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion about the post please call John Woodman, General Manager on 01274 366181.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;CLOSING DATE:                               20th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INTERVIEW DATE:                           &lt;/strong&gt;1st December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
